description: From green +‎ -th. Cognate with Dutch groente.

entries.meaning: The state or quality of being green; verdure, verdancy.
examples: Imagine a rambling, patchy house,  […]  the mellow darkness of its conical roof surmounted by a weather-cock making an agreeable object either amidst the gleams and greenth of summer or the low-hanging clouds and snowy branches of winter  […]
